## Scalability Strategy

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### Desktop Scalability

- **Local Data**: Handle 100,000+ records
- **Multi-threading**: Utilize all CPU cores
- **Memory Efficiency**: Lazy loading and pagination
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### Cloud Scalability

- **Auto-Scaling**: Lambda concurrency + ALB targets
- **Database Scaling**: Read replicas, sharding strategy
- **Caching Layer**: ElastiCache for session and data
- **Queue-Based Processing**: SQS for async operations
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if tauri-aws}} -->
### Hybrid Scalability

- **Desktop**: Local performance regardless of user count
- **Cloud**: Auto-scaling backend for sync operations
- **Sync Optimization**: Batch updates, delta sync
<!-- {{/if}} -->

## Deployment Architecture

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### Desktop Deployment

```
GitHub Actions
    → Build for all platforms (Windows, macOS, Linux)
    → Code signing
    → Generate installers (.dmg, .msi, .AppImage)
    → Upload to GitHub Releases
    → Tauri updater manifest
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### Web Deployment

```
GitHub Actions
    → Run tests and linting
    → Build Next.js app
    → Deploy infrastructure (CDK)
        ├── Frontend → S3 + CloudFront
        ├── API → Lambda + API Gateway
        └── Database → RDS
    → Run smoke tests
    → Notify team
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

